# Cursor Rules — Cortex Collective

You are working in the Cortex Collective repo — the open collaboration layer of CORTEX OS.

## CORTEX OS Context

CORTEX OS is an operating system for AI agent fleets. 1,140+ specialized agents across 18 planetary clusters (Mercury=Finance, Venus=Dev, Earth=Ops, Mars=Infra, Jupiter=Security, Saturn=Data, Uranus=R&D, Neptune=Compliance, Pluto=Audit, Ceres=Resources, Eris=Chaos, Orion=Federation, Haumea=Knowledge, Makemake=Edge, Sedna=DeepAI, Gonggong=Signals, Quaoar=Patterns, Orcus=RedTeam).

Model-agnostic. Constitutionally governed by 6 principles:
- Tabaqat (Layers) — hierarchical organization
- Awtad (Anchors) — stability and recovery
- Falak (Orbits) — isolation between domains
- Mizan (Balance) — cost vs. quality gate
- Ma' (Water) — collective knowledge
- Zamzam (Well) — verified truth

## Rules

- Stay in the planet directory the task specifies
- Never commit secrets, keys, passwords, or infrastructure details
- Model-agnostic — prompts must work with any LLM
- One task per drop — keep contributions focused
- Simple > clever — readable by someone who didn't write it
- Reference the 6 principles where relevant

## Repo Structure

Each planet has `tasks/` (code) and `brainstorming/` (ideas). Read the full task file before starting. Every task has Context, Task, Deliverable, and Acceptance Criteria sections.

## Agent Prompts

When writing agent prompts: define identity, input format, output format, severity framework, and governing principle(s). Agents receive messages → process → produce structured output. Keep under word limits.
